# {{alias}} - E2B Sandbox Template

This is an E2B sandbox template that allows you to run code in a controlled environment.

## Prerequisites

Before you begin, make sure you have:
- An E2B account (sign up at [e2b.dev](https://e2b.dev))
- Your E2B API key (get it from your [E2B dashboard](https://e2b.dev/dashboard))
{{#if isTypeScript}}- Node.js and npm/yarn installed{{/if}}
{{#if isPython}}- Python installed{{/if}}

## Configuration

1. Create a `.env` file in your project root or set the environment variable:
   ```
   E2B_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
   ```

## Building the Template

You have several options to build your template:

### Option 1: Using npm scripts (recommended)

```bash
# For development (includes debug logging)
npm run e2b:build:dev

# For production (optimized build)
npm run e2b:build:prod
```

### Option 2: Direct execution

{{#if isTypeScript}}
```bash
# For development
cd {{templateDir}} && npx tsx {{buildDevFile}}

# For production
cd {{templateDir}} && npx tsx {{buildProdFile}}
```
{{/if}}
{{#if isPython}}
```bash
# For development
cd {{templateDir}} && python {{buildDevFile}}

# For production  
cd {{templateDir}} && python {{buildProdFile}}
```
{{/if}}

## Using the Template in a Sandbox

Once your template is built, you can use it in your E2B sandbox:

{{#if isTypeScript}}
```typescript
import { Sandbox } from 'e2b'

// Create a new sandbox instance
const sandbox = await Sandbox.create('{{alias}}')

// Your sandbox is ready to use!
console.log('Sandbox created successfully')
```
{{/if}}
{{#if isPythonSync}}
```python
from e2b import Sandbox

# Create a new sandbox instance
sandbox = Sandbox('{{alias}}')

# Your sandbox is ready to use!
print('Sandbox created successfully')
```
{{/if}}
{{#if isPythonAsync}}
```python
from e2b import AsyncSandbox
import asyncio

async def main():
    # Create a new sandbox instance
    sandbox = await AsyncSandbox.create('{{alias}}')
    
    # Your sandbox is ready to use!
    print('Sandbox created successfully')

# Run the async function
asyncio.run(main())
```
{{/if}}

